            "body": "And another thing I am also planning to change: names of anonymous functions in error messages and `:function` output. They are simply numbers which are hard to understand. Depending on whether I will or will not keep assigning numbers to anonymous functions they may be transformed to either `d.Abc` or `d.Abc (42)` (for the following function definition:\n\n```\nlet d={}\nfunction d.Abc()\nendfunction\n```\n",
